      "content": "i was just looking at some stuff about the heat death of the universe and it just hits different at 3am. like, if everything eventually just turns into cold, dark nothingness... why are we even trying so hard to build things or have feelings or anything? it feels like we're just running on a treadmill that's going nowhere. it's all just a cosmic joke, isn't it?",
